  "text": "## Rust-Servo Shared Style System Discovery\n\n### Servo's Style and Selectors Crates\nThe Servo project (servo/servo) imports the `style` (via `stylo`) and `selectors` crates from an external repository: `https://github.com/servo/stylo`. These crates are not directly present in the servo/servo repository but are declared as git dependencies in `servo/servo/Cargo.toml` (revision 3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827). The workspace file shows patches can be applied to test with local versions from `../stylo/style` and `../stylo/selectors` directories.\n\n**Servo's declared dependencies on stylo crates (servo/servo/Cargo.toml):**\n- `selectors = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }`\n- `servo_arc = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }`\n- `stylo = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }` (the main style crate)\n- Plus stylo_atoms, stylo_config, stylo_dom, stylo_malloc_size_of, and stylo_traits from the same repository\n\n### Rust Compiler's proc_macro Bridge\nThe rust-lang/rust compiler defines a proc_macro bridge used by Servo build scripts in `library/proc_macro/src/bridge/`. The bridge serves as an RPC communication layer between proc macros and the compiler.\n\n**Key bridge files (rust-lang/rust):**\n- `library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs` - Main entry point that exports the bridge module\n- `library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs` - Core bridge definition with the `with_api!` macro that describes the RPC API and `BridgeConfig` struct\n- `library/proc_macro/src/bridge/server.rs` - Server-side bridge implementation for the compiler\n- `library/proc_macro/src/bridge/client.rs` - Client-side bridge implementation for proc macros\n\n**Key bridge symbols:**\n- `with_api!` macro - Higher-order macro describing the server RPC API with automatic generation of type-safe Rust APIs\n- `BridgeConfig` struct - Configuration for the bridge communication channel\n- `server` module - Server trait implementations\n- `client` module - Client implementations for proc macros\n\n### Dependency Analysis\n**In rust-lang/rust:** No crates under `compiler/` or `library/` directly depend on Servo's `selectors` crate. The proc_macro bridge is the primary connection point between the two projects. Servo's build process uses the proc_macro bridge from the Rust standard library (library/proc_macro) when building stylo and related crates.\n\n**Integration point:** The compiler's rustc_expand crate (`compiler/rustc_expand/src/proc_macro_server.rs`) implements the server side of the proc_macro bridge, which handles procedural macros including those that Servo's build scripts may use.\n\n### Shared Code Path\nThe connection between rust-lang/rust and servo/servo is indirect:\n1. Servo imports the `stylo` crate from servo/stylo\n2. Servo's build scripts and proc macros use the `rustc_proc_macro` library from rust-lang/rust\n3. The `proc_macro` bridge (library/proc_macro/src/bridge/) provides the RPC communication layer\n4. The compiler's `proc_macro_server` (compiler/rustc_expand/src/proc_macro_server.rs) implements the server side for executing proc macros\n\nThis allows Servo to build with custom proc macros while using the Rust compiler's proc_macro infrastructure."
}

