nfig` struct - Configuration for the bridge communication channel\n- `server` module - Server trait implementations\n- `client` module - Client implementations for proc macros\n\n### Dependency Analysis\n**In rust-lang/rust:** No crates under `compiler/` or `library/` directly depend on Servo's `selectors` crate. The proc_macro bridge is the primary connection point between the two projects. Servo's build process uses the proc_macro bridge from the Rust standard library (library/proc_macro) when building stylo and related crates.\n\n**Integration point:** The compiler's rustc_expand crate (`compiler/rustc_expand/src/proc_macro_server.rs`) implements the server side of the proc_macro bridge, which handles procedural macros including those that Servo's build scripts may use.\n\n### Shared Code Path\nThe connection between rust-lang/rust and servo/servo is indirect:\n1. Servo imports the `stylo` crate from servo/stylo\n2. Servo's build scripts and proc macros use the `rustc_proc_macro` library from rust-lang/rust\n3. The `proc_macro` bridge (library/proc_macro/src/bridge/) provides the RPC communication layer\n4. The compiler's `proc_macro_server` (compiler/rustc_expand/src/proc_macro_server.rs) implements the server side for executing proc macros\n\nThis allows Servo to build with custom proc macros while using the Rust compiler's proc_macro infrastructure."
